    17→{"display":"i should add - the treasury team meeting last night was good - i am surprised sometimes by how much i disgree with Will on implementation details of plans.  Keith, the EMEA RVC, came to the meeting to discuss a means by which non country committees (NCC's) can fundraise and spend money as if they were a country committee. I suggested the 3 regional vice chairs all be treated as defacto managers of a NCC sub acount for each region and have flexibility to manage however is best for each region.  Will felt strongly that we set up individual sub accounts for each potential NCC while still having the RVC and NCC DPCA representative manage the budget/spending for each one.  I tried to Keith to comment on which he would prefer, but he (possibly wisely and diplomatically) did not respond.  Will is the person who will end up managing the new sub accounts and adding them into the python scrips he uses to integrate nationbuilder and expense tracking with quickbooks, so I defer to him.  but it bothers me that I can seem to convince anyone of doing things incrementally and with the minimal amount of administrative work, especially as everyone is always complaining how much volunteer admin work there is.  but will thinks it's easier - which i think is born from his familiarity with the python scripts he uses.  Anyway, the meeting last 2 hours so i did not get to sleep until after 11pm.  i really enjoy being on the treasury team, more than i did on the IT team, but i also wonder what my real impact is.","pastedContents":{},"timestamp":1770167832065,"project":"/Users/bmc/vaults/knowledge-base","sessionId":"6baf3d92-07c5-43f9-9beb-3975eb114955"}
    18→{"display":"i'm sure in will's mind and perhaps arguably so the incremental approach is to create sub accounts on an as needed basis. the accountant kathy argued agains introducing regional level accounts as she thought it would require creating new hierarchies in the books, which i did not think would be neccessary - the RVC is not responsible for the elected country committee sub accounts - but i see will's point about just adding new sub accounts as needed is probably simpler for him. it can probably even be automated to a degree. ","pastedContents":{},"timestamp":1770168279183,"project":"/Users/bmc/vaults/knowledge-base","sessionId":"6baf3d92-07c5-43f9-9beb-3975eb114955"}
